%N A389427 a(n) = Sum_{i=1..n} (Product_{j=1..n} M(j, ((i+j-2) mod n)+1) - Product_{j=1..n} M(j, ((i-j-1) mod n)+1)) where M is the n X n matrix M(n) formed by writing the numbers 1, ..., n^2 successively forward and backward along the rows in zig-zag pattern.
%C A389427 The definition generalizes the rule of Sarrus to matrices of order different than 3.
%H A389427 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rule_of_Sarrus">Rule of Sarrus</a>.
